 SECOND APPEL AUX COMMUNICATIONS       SECOND CALL FOR PAPERS

                                   JFLA2001
               Journées Francophones des Langages Applicatifs
               French Speaking Conference on Applicative Programming Languages


                        INRIA, LaBRI (Bordeaux)

                        29 et 30  janvier 2001     
	                January 29th and 30th 2001  




 English text
 (Version Francaise plus bas)


JFLA'2001 is the 12th french speaking conference on applicative programming
languages; it will take place in the French Jura (sic) mountains, in the
city of Pontarlier.

The JFLA conferences aim to make designers and users of applicative 
languages meet in a nice place. Traditionnaly, the topics cover all
theoretical and practical aspects of applicative languages; 
moreover, the JFLA reiterate their interest in proof assistants,
 the development of which has been, for a long time, linked with 
applicative programming.  Teaching of programming is an important 
topic too.

Here is a (non exclusive) list of topics :

 Functional programming : semantics, compiling, optimization,
 testing, extensions by other paradigms,

 Specification, prototyping, formal developments of algorithms,
  industrial use of applicative languages,

 Proof assistants : implementation, new tactics, examples of developments
 which present some technical:methodological interest,

 Applicative programming and teaching of computer science.


  
Invited Speakers
----------------
  Gilles Dowek (Projet Coq, INRIA Rocquencourt)
  Christian Queinnec (LIP6)



